title: Abdel Latif Fatihi
text: Abdel Latif Fatihi (born 23 April 1951) is a Moroccan <a href="boxing">boxer</a>. He competed in the <a href="Boxing%20at%20the%201976%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Light%20heavyweight">men's light heavyweight</a> event at the <a href="1976%20Summer%20Olympics">1976 Summer Olympics</a>. His only bout was a round-of-32 match versus <a href="Leon%20Spinks">Leon Spinks</a> of the United States. Spinks, the eventual gold medalist, won by a first-round knockout.
